I want learn github. Can you create a roadmap to learn in one month with daily plan, and resources for learning including links?

Certainly! Here is a one-month roadmap for learning GitHub, with daily tasks and resources:

Week 1:
Day 1: Introduction to Git and GitHub
Familiarize yourself with the basic concepts of Git and GitHub.
Watch the "What is Git?" video on the official Git website: https://git-scm.com/video/what-is-git
Read the "GitHub Explained" guide on the official GitHub website: https://guides.github.com/activities/hello-world/

Day 2: Creating a GitHub account
Create a GitHub account.
Verify your email address and add a profile picture and description.
Explore the GitHub user interface and understand its basic features.

Day 3: Creating a repository
Learn how to create a new repository on GitHub.
Familiarize yourself with the various repository settings, including collaboration and access control.
Follow the "Create a repo" guide on the official GitHub website: https://docs.github.com/en/github/getting-started-with-github/create-a-repo

Day 4: Cloning a repository
Learn how to clone an existing repository to your local machine.
Familiarize yourself with the various Git commands used to clone a repository.
Follow the "Cloning a repository" guide on the official GitHub website: https://docs.github.com/en/github/creating-cloning-and-archiving-repositories/cloning-a-repository

Day 5: Basic Git commands
Learn the basic Git commands, including adding, committing, and pushing changes to a repository.
Familiarize yourself with the various Git workflows, including the centralized and distributed models.
Read the "Git Basics" guide on the official Git website: https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Basics-Getting-a-Git-Repository

Week 2:
Day 6: Branching and merging
Learn how to create and manage branches in Git.
Familiarize yourself with the various merging strategies, including fast-forward and non-fast-forward merges.
Read the "Git Branching" guide on the official Git website: https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Branching-Branches-in-a-Nutshell

Day 7: Collaborating on GitHub
Learn how to collaborate on a GitHub repository with other users.
Familiarize yourself with the various collaboration workflows, including pull requests and issues.
Follow the "Collaborating with issues and pull requests" guide on the official GitHub website: https://docs.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests

Week 3:
Day 8: GitHub Pages
Learn how to create a website using GitHub Pages.
Familiarize yourself with the various templates and customization options available.
Follow the "Creating a GitHub Pages site" guide on the official GitHub website: https://docs.github.com/en/pages/getting-started-with-github-pages/creating-a-github-pages-site

Day 9: GitHub Actions
Learn how to use GitHub Actions to automate tasks and workflows.
Familiarize yourself with the various pre-built actions and customizing workflows.
Follow the "Getting started with GitHub Actions" guide on the official GitHub website: https://docs.github.com/en/actions/learn-github-actions/getting-started-with-github-actions

Day 10: Advanced Git commands
Learn the advanced Git commands, including rebasing, cherry-picking, and tagging.
Familiarize yourself with the various Git workflows used in large-scale projects.
Read the "Advanced Git" guide on the official Git website: https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Tools-Advanced-Merging
